1
00:00:02,966 --> 00:00:04,434
But let's see what the Bible says.

2
00:00:04,434 --> 00:00:05,501
Yes, let's.

3
00:00:05,501 --> 00:00:09,138
In Exodus 21:22-24 we read,

4
00:00:09,138 --> 00:00:11,574
"When men strive
together and hit a pregnant woman

5
00:00:11,574 --> 00:00:14,577
so that her children
come out, but there is no harm,

6
00:00:14,577 --> 00:00:16,980
the one who hit
her shall surely be fined,

7
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:19,449
as the woman's
husband shall impose on him,

8
00:00:19,449 --> 00:00:22,185
and he shall pay as the judges determine.

9
00:00:22,185 --> 00:00:25,621
But if there is harm,
then you shall pay life for life,

10
00:00:25,621 --> 00:00:28,391
eye for eye, tooth
for tooth, hand for hand,

11
00:00:28,391 --> 00:00:30,460
foot for foot, burn for burn,

12
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:33,096
wound for wound, striped for stripe.

13
00:00:33,096 --> 00:00:34,831
So there was an additional penalty

14
00:00:34,831 --> 00:00:37,133
if an unborn child was harmed.

15
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:39,635
Note the term
children, not clumps of cells.

16
00:00:39,635 --> 00:00:43,206
- Yeah, the late first
century Christian work Didachē

17
00:00:43,206 --> 00:00:46,609
says, "The second
commandment of the teaching,

18
00:00:46,609 --> 00:00:49,479
you shall not murder,
you shall not commit adultery,

19
00:00:49,479 --> 00:00:50,980
you shall not seduce boys,

20
00:00:50,980 --> 00:00:52,615
you shall not commit fornication,

21
00:00:52,615 --> 00:00:55,585
you shall not steal,
you shall not practice magic,

22
00:00:55,585 --> 00:00:57,453
you shall not use potions,

23
00:00:57,453 --> 00:00:59,589
you shall not procure an abortion,

24
00:00:59,589 --> 00:01:01,958
nor destroy a newborn child."

25
00:01:01,958 --> 00:01:04,560
- God considers the
preborn child to be human

26
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:06,529
and worthy of his attention.

27
00:01:06,529 --> 00:01:10,133
In Genesis 25:23, God tells Rebecca,

28
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:11,801
"Two nations are in your womb,

29
00:01:11,801 --> 00:01:14,570
and two peoples from
within you shall be divided.

30
00:01:14,570 --> 00:01:16,439
The one shall be stronger than the other,

31
00:01:16,439 --> 00:01:18,675
the older shall serve the younger."

32
00:01:18,675 --> 00:01:20,677
- Later, God says to Jeremiah,

33
00:01:20,677 --> 00:01:23,046
"Before I formed
you in the womb, I knew you,

34
00:01:23,046 --> 00:01:25,982
and before you were
born, I consecrated you.

35
00:01:25,982 --> 00:01:28,651
I appointed you a
prophet to the nations."

